### Variable Configuration
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8181/api/v1/auth

//@baseUrl = http://localhost:8181/api/v1/auth

@contentType = application/json

### 1. Register a new user (Register)
# This method will encrypt the password and save the user in login_user
POST {{baseUrl}}/register
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
    "email": "obiwan_kenobi@spring.com",
    "password": "Luminos0!",
    "userName": "Obiwan",
    "lastName": "Kenobi",
    "authProvider": "LOCAL",
    "roleUser": "ROLE_USER"
}

### 2. Log in (Login)
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
    "email": "obiwan_kenobi@spring.com",
    "password": "Luminos0!"
}

### Save the previous login token
@authToken = {{login.response.body.token}}

### 3. Example test for a protected route (Optional)
# Once you have other controllers, use this structure to test the JWT
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/customers
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}